cs.SD, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the joint processing of audio and visual data, which suggests it could belong to several sub-categories. 

- cs.SD (Sound): This sub-category deals with audio processing and analysis, which is directly relevant to the paper's focus on separating and analyzing sound components. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): This sub-category deals with image and video analysis, which is also relevant to the paper's focus on locating image regions that produce sounds. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): This sub-category deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data, which is directly relevant to the paper's focus on joint audio-visual processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category deals with the development and application of machine learning algorithms, which is relevant to the paper's use of unsupervised learning to process large amounts of unlabeled data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category deals with the development and application of AI algorithms, which is relevant to the paper's use of deep learning to process audio-visual data.
